### Actual Output:
@startuml marekq_rss-lambda
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor "User" as user

rectangle "CloudWatch Events" as cw_events
rectangle "Step Function" as step_function
rectangle "Lambda\nrsscrawl" as lambda_crawl
rectangle "Lambda\nrssgetfeed" as lambda_getfeed
rectangle "Lambda\npagecount" as lambda_pagecount
rectangle "DynamoDB" as dynamodb
rectangle "S3" as s3
rectangle "AppSync" as appsync
rectangle "Algolia" as algolia
rectangle "SES" as ses
rectangle "Comprehend" as comprehend

user --> lambda_pagecount : Manual Invoke
cw_events --> step_function : Scheduled Trigger
step_function --> lambda_crawl : Start Crawl
lambda_crawl --> s3 : Check existing data
lambda_crawl --> step_function : Feed URLs
step_function --> lambda_getfeed : Process Feed (Fan-out)
lambda_getfeed --> comprehend : Entity Recognition
lambda_getfeed --> dynamodb : Store post data
lambda_getfeed --> ses : Send Notification (optional)
lambda_getfeed --> s3 : Store public JSON (optional)
lambda_getfeed --> algolia : Index post (optional)
dynamodb --> appsync : GraphQL API
appsync --> user : Data Access

note right of step_function
  State Machine Orchestration
  with Fan-out/Fan-in pattern
end note

note right of lambda_getfeed
  Content Extraction Pipeline:
  1. Fetch RSS feed
  2. Extract content
  3. Enrich with Comprehend
  4. Store/Notify/Index
end note
@enduml